The 1980s ==

With the release of her Feel The Fire album in 1980, Claudja's songs were becoming highly synthesized – this was her final album to feature an earthier, more horn & string approach to the production of her music.
In 1981, she made a successful foray into new wave/Hi-NRG music with the album Made in Hong Kong.
In 1985, she appeared in the movie, Rappin', starring Mario Van Peebles.
The year 1985 also saw the release of the single, "Born To Love" which sounds similar to a Pet Shop Boys or Erasure song.
On the Hot Dance Music/Club Play chart, she has had much more success: six Top 10 hits, including "Down and Counting", which spent a week at No. 1 in 1986.

The 1990s ==
She still remained active recording a pair of underground club classics during the early 1990s.
The singles "Love Is An Island" (1991) and "Summer of Love" (1992) are highly regarded club hits to those who know them.

== 1999 to present ==
